{
  "name": "Discern Condition",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "modules/pf1spheres/assets/icons/spheres/scout.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You may use the scout ability to determine the relative health and condition of a creature within line of sight and effect in addition to the normal information provided by your scout ability. You determine the creature&#8217;s condition based on the list below:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Normal:</strong> Has at least 90% of full normal hit points, free of disease.</li>\n<li><strong>Fair:</strong> 30% to 90% of full normal hit points remaining.</li>\n<li><strong>Poor:</strong> Less than 30% of full normal hit points remaining, afflicted with a disease, or suffering from a debilitating injury.</li>\n<li><strong>Weak:</strong> 0 or fewer hit points remaining, afflicted with a disease that has reduced an ability score to 5 or less, or crippled.</li>\n</ul>\n",
